==Finnish==

===Case suffix===
''Depending on the preceding vowel:''
'''-an''', '''-en''', '''-in''', '''-on''', '''-un''', '''-yn''', '''-än''', '''-ön'''

# Forms the [[illative]] singular case.

====Usage====
Used after an unstressed short vowel. The vowel is the same as the final vowel in the stem, thus producing a long vowel.

====Examples====
: '''word''' : '''(strong) vowel stem''' : '''illative'''
: ''[[jalka]]'' : ''jalka-'' : ''jalkaan''
: ''[[miniä]]'' : ''miniä-'' : ''miniään''
: ''[[oikea]]'' : ''oikea-'' : ''oikeaan''
: ''[[tuli#Finnish|tuli]]'' : ''tule-'' : ''tuleen''

